                           <locus from="3ra" to="3vc">ff. 3ra-3vc</locus>
                           <locus from="176va" to="177vb">ff. 176va-177vb</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText"><title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2807RepCh91">salām-hymns for Mary</title></desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                               ሰላምለኪ፡ ማርያም፡ ድንግል፡ ዘመአዛ፡ አፉኪ፡ ኮል፡
                              እንተ፡ ትጼንዊ፡ በገዳም፡ ወሐቅል፡ …</q>
                           <note>The note starts on <locus target="#3ra">3ra</locus>, interrupts on <locus target="#3vc">3vc</locus> and
                           continues on <locus from="176va" to="177vb">176va-177vb</locus>. It
                           contains rubrications. Readings for it are indicated mostly by the
                           moments of the days, written in the upper margin (in a frame of two lines
                           below and above): በልኒ፡ (above), ዘነግህ (below): <locus target="#3r">3r</locus> ዘቀትር (left), ዘ፱ሰዓት (right): <locus target="#3v">3v</locus>
                           ዘሰርክ (left), ዘንዋም (right): <locus target="#176v">176v</locus> ዘሌሊት:
                              <locus target="#177r">177r</locus>. The note ends with a short
                           colophon (<locus target="#177vc">177vc</locus>
                           )with the name of the scribe, i.e. Walda ʾAbrǝha. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#77vc">f. 77vc (below the text)</locus>
                           <desc type="GuarantorsList">List of personal names.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="am">
                             ለየአቶ፡ ኃፍቱ፡ ቤት፡ …</q>
                           <note> The note is written in pen. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc type="Correction">Corrections (words or letters) written interlineally:
                           e.g., <locus target="#6rb">6rb</locus>, 6rc, 12va, 16va, 80rc, 172rc,
                           175ra.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc type="Correction">Corrections marked by dots around the words: <locus target="#90ra">90ra</locus> and 161vc.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc type="Correction">Corrections written over
                           erasure: <locus target="#123rc">123rc</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc>Pen trial: <locus target="#66va">66va</locus> (below the text).</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5"><desc>A crude note in
                           pen and in a recent hand is on <locus target="#66vb">66vb</locus>.
                           Another note in the same hand, erased, is on <locus target="#66vc">66vc</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc type="findingAid">The word ሕዝበ፡ is written in the main hand in the
                              upper margin of <locus target="#89r">fol. 89r</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e7"><desc> Crude notes,
                              concerning the main text, are written in pencil and in a recent hand
                              in the upper margins of fols. 90v-91v, 106v. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e8"><desc>Notes have been erased
                              in the upper margin of fols. 97r and 161v. </desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards covered with reddish-brown tooled
                           leather; textile inlays.
 Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                           <material key="textile"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">Blind tooled ornament on the reddish-brown leather
                           cover (at least 6 tools were used: triple line fillet, double circle,
                           x-form, wave form, double sine wave with dots, cross hatching) and on the
                           turn-ins (at least 2 tools were used: triple line fillet, double
                           circle).</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b6" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b7" type="Other">Cotton thread is inserted
                           at the edge of <locus target="#107">fol. 107</locus>, for navigating
                           in the text.</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
